{{Quote|24-player action-packed PVP shooter where you can plot a plan to organize a Heist with your friends or defend the casino from the Robbersǃ Currently on Alpha‚ bugs are expected in this build․}}

'''Heist''' is a player-versus-player action 
[[Special:MyLanguage/:Category:Game worlds|game world]]
created by ''miru_kitsune'' in 2024. Up to 24 players are able to participate in one of two teams. Robbers must steal valuables from a casino, while the Guards seek them, and stop the robbers in their tracks. Heist is built using a system coded in [[Udon]], and the game has is considered in alpha status since May, 2024.

== Win conditions ==
===Robbers===
Steal from the casino without dying and escape.
===Guards===
Kill all the robbers before they escape.
===Bystanders===
Collect clues to become a guard or steal loot to become a robber.                                                                                   
== Suspicion ==
There are two suspicion statues. 
===Suspicious===
You become suspicious if you:
* Have stolen loot.
* Have weapons out.
* Enter staff-only areas.
* Stand close to the escape van.
===Hunted===
You will become hunted if you:
* Steal the main loot.
* Get exposed by clues.
* Escape the casino.
*

